ArrayList (Dynamic Array) 📦
🧠 Logic:ArrayList Java Collections Framework ka part hai. Yeh ek resizable array hai, jiska matlab hai ki yeh $\mathbf{dynamic}$ roop se size badha aur ghata sakta hai. Jabki traditional arrays ka size $\mathbf{fixed}$ hota hai.ArrayList sirf Objects (non-primitive types, jaise Integer, String) store karta hai, primitive types (int, char) nahi.📌 Example:Javaimport java.util.ArrayList;

// Integer type ke elements ke liye ArrayList banaya
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(); 

// Elements add karna
list.add(10);
list.add(20);

// Elements access karna
System.out.println(list.get(0)); // 10

// Size badal gaya
list.add(30);
System.out.println(list.size()); // 3
🔤 Java Code:Javaimport java.util.ArrayList;

public class ArrayListDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // String type ka ArrayList
        ArrayList<String> fruits = new ArrayList<>();
        
        // Add elements
        fruits.add("Apple"); 
        fruits.add("Banana"); 
        fruits.add("Orange"); 

        // Print the full list
        System.out.println("List: " + fruits); 

        // Remove element by index (Banana hat jayega)
        fruits.remove(1);
        
        // Check if an element exists
        System.out.println("Contains Apple? " + fruits.contains("Apple")); // true

        // Print list after removal
        System.out.println("After removal: " + fruits);
    }
}
/* Output:
List: [Apple, Banana, Orange]
Contains Apple? true
After removal: [Apple, Orange]
*/
🧾 Notebook Points:Java📘 ArrayList:
→ Resizable/Dynamic Array
→ Fixed size nahi hota
→ Collections Framework ka hissa

🔢 Methods: add(), get(index), remove(index), size()
